rounds.response:
Let me first figure out how every one of my resources is currently valued on a *per-unit* basis so I know what I can afford to give away and what I should be trying to obtain.

Value/unit:
• Wheat: 6 / 8  = 0.75
• Wood: 12 / 5 = 2.4
• Sheep: 16 / 13 ≈ 1.23
• Brick: 20 / 8 = 2.5
• Ore: 32 / 11 ≈ 2.91

So in increasing value per unit:  
Wheat < Sheep < Wood < Brick < Ore.

Looking at the incoming offer from Player 0:  
[1 Ore → 3 Brick]

Player 0 is offering the highest-value-per-unit resource (Ore) for 3 units of the second-highest-value-per-unit resource (Brick).  
Calculation:

- What I would give: 3 Brick → value lost = 3 × 2.5 = 7.5  
- What I would receive: 1 Ore → value gained = 2.91  

The trade *loses* 7.5 – 2.91 = 4.6 units of value.  
Therefore I should reject it.  

[Deny]
